Another interesting concept is that some coins can be represented as tokens on other networks. For ex - Binance pegged #ETH token on Binance smart chain represents the value of #ETH. People buy this instead of the coin to mostly save on gas fees (Network fees for transactions).

Notably, the famous Shiba Inu(#SHIB) is a token built on the #Ethereum blockchain and is not a coin whereas Dogecoin(#doge) is a coin having its own blockchain.

Although this may not have any direct effect on the value that they represent.

The best example is #Ethereum, It has its own blockchain that both stores value and validates transactions. An Ethereum token or an ERC20 token uses Ethereum's blockchain capabilities as its infrastructure. For Ex- #USDT (tether) is an ERC20 token and not a coin.
